description: {DThis portion of the dark forest is littered with the remains of
numerous fallen trees and limbs.  Something massive has crashed
through the wooden giants, splintering them in vicious impact only to
cast them wrathfully to the floor of the Karasuthra.  The moon
gleefully peers through a noticeably gap in the canopy, gloating in
the malady that has befallen its eternal foes.  The ground is broken
and cluttered, no sign of the source is apparent.  {x

description: {DDebris litters the Karasuthra floor, a mish-mash of torn canopy,

dark mire.  Blast marks mar the surviving trees, illuminated by the
65597.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

description: {DAn arboreal wall grows from the dimly lit forest floor to the dark

to lilt downward like energetic snow, before winking out ere ever
65592.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

terribly disturbed by the encroaching light, going on about their
65609.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

heavens.  The ruckus of fighting animals shake the nearby shrubs and
65630.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

trunks.  Wild orchids grow within the crenulous bark at unreachable

in a luminous glow.  Branches clack softly together under the caress

65510.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

points or from a beast merely marking territory, it is difficult to
65527.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

description: {DThis range of the Beastlands is known as the Karasuthra, a
demi-plane of endless night, lit only by the meager glow of the waxing
and waning silvered moon.  It's forested expanse is populated by the
creatures which primarily become active at night.  A constant tense
sensation of being watched, nay, of being hunted, fills the night air.
65504.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

description: {DVines tendril about the trunks of a collection of dark elms,
weaving and interlacing across the timbers.  A steady stream of leaves

Karasuthra bed is littered with the detritus cast off by the countless
trees, making tracking difficult through the mass of needles, mulch
65618.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

description: {DThe ominous chatter of nocturnal predators and prey fills the
eternal night forest.  The Karasuthra is filled with participants of
the great hunt, each playing the part of predator and prey in their

65604.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

piercing caresses against the eternal night floor before being blocked
65602.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

fragrant night lillies.  Greedy eyes follow the movements of the

65588.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

description: {DYowls of terror or rage echo through the darkness, followed by a

65611.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

description: {DUmbrage trees cavort and writhe in the light touch of a caressing
wind.  Little can be seen the farther up one glances, for the trees

awaiting the opportunity to ambush.  The hunt in the Karasuthra

65631.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

collection of towering rocks, each standing several spans higher than
65537.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

trees, permenantly shrouding the base of Karasuthra in an ominous
65562.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

shielding the forest about it from the watchful eye of the lazy
65512.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

track movement from the shadows, awaiting the chance to launch an
65613.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

nearby taller neighbors.  Each grows to an expanse which seems to

and screams fill the darkness, as the predator and prey meet in
65513.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

{DFar from providing light, the moonbeams seem to enrich the darkness

65594.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

the dance of the hunt throughout the branches of the immense trees and
65626.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

Crimson eyes peer from the heights of the sheltering boughs, tracking
65532.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

65517.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

illuminated by the silvery rays of moonlight streaking down from the
65534.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

65529.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

ever-present eyes of unseen predators watch, picking out the weakest
65521.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

65619.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

across the expanse of a fallen tree, marching into the heights of the
65555.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

of the hunters pierce the darkness, tracking movements through the
65525.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

present danger of the predators certain to be ne The rustle of night

65515.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

the fallen detritus of the high canopy.  The hoots and yowls of night
65621.name: {DW{ci{gt{Dh{gin K{Da{cr{Da{gsu{Dt{ghr{ca{x

neverending dance.  The signs of pursuit are all around.  The RUSTLE

description:
{DThe Feli are a race of humanoid cat-people that inhabit many parts
of the realm, but seem to have a large population inhabiting the
depths of the Karasuthra where their feline attributes are of great
benefit.  Covered from head to toe in short, brindle striped hair,
this Feli brings a clawed paw up to a bewhiskered face to clean
himself, as only a cat can.  A lashing tail whips about, betraying the
nervous nature of the creature.  Somewhat shorter than an average
human, yet larger than a dwarf, the Feli are lithe of stature and well
proportioned.  {x

{DExotic to behold, this Caterwauler is covered in short silvered
white fur, with a black mask and points.  Her dark blue fluid eyes

Her Feli tail swishes about in anxiety, as she pinpoints something of

{DSomewhat larger than the average Feli, the Pouncers are a lot more

branchers, where they can prepare ambushes without being seen,
Pouncer's enjoy dropping on unsuspecting victims.  Orange fur
burnished with deep black stripes covers a finely muscled form. 
Pearly white teeth smile from a wild set face.  Golden hued eyes peer

description:
{DUmbral banyans are sentient trees commonly found on the Plane of
Shadow, however, owing to the proximity of Karasuthra's eternal dark
forest to that of Shadow, they often cross over and hunt the forests. 
Upon glance, there is little to distinguish the umbral from
surrounding trees, allowing it to freely ambush foolish creatures
whensoever they fall into its grasp.  It is said that these trees are
quite aggressive, subdueing their prey with wicked blows of their
wooden arms, before retreating to the shadows to devour their booty.  {x

description:
{DNative to the Plane of Shadow, the ecalypse often traverse the
divide through the numerous connective portals to cavort in the
forests of the Karasuthra at their leisure.  Wild and fickle, these
horselike creatures enjoy the liberties of the eternal night, and oft
have little to fear from the hunters surrounding them.  Their forms
are largely insubstantial and colorless, but if one were to peer
closely enough, six rangey legs ending in hooves, connected to a
strong horselike body and head would be seen.

the beast finds itself threatened.  Proportionally, one could hardly
believe something so very small could become this huge, and yet, it is
now quite mammoth.  It's golden fur has become burn brownish and much
shaggier.  Massive tusks now jut from its mouth, curling inward toward
its own face.  Once tiny mothlike wings have become gigantic in span
and size, large enough to support the Mastodon body in flight.  {x {DPure
rage colours its features, it has gone berserk.  {x

{DFar from the centaurs found on the prime plane, this centaur is
more of a kin with the centaur's which inhabit the light sub-realms of
the Beastlands.  It's ears are much longer, its equine features
sleeker and more muscular, lending to its life in the eternal wilds. 
Though somewhat smaller than a standard, prime-bound centaur, by
comparison, these beasts are far more wily and feral.  This hunter has
entered the Karasuthra on a sacred tracking mission, though it is
unlikely that the timid creature will reveal it.  {x

eternal darkness has caused a shift in the dryads' pattern of living,

creatures have adapted the ability to create their own illumination,
oft with visually appealing effects.  The ghaele are celestial
creatures that work on behalf of goodness in its battle against
wickedness.  They are beings of light, most oft appearing as globes of

direct and confronational, preferring to take on a challenge head on

description:
{DThe therianthropes of the Beastlands are different from the
lycanthropes that frequent the Prime Materia.  For all intensive
purposes, these beasts are far more feral and less humane in their
form and abilities.  Oft seen wandering about on all fours, closer in
gait to their animal spirit than the two-legged stride.  Many
therianthropes are ascended lycanthropes that no longer have the
ability to transform between forms.  Others are simply animals that
have transcended to a greater celestial form and maintain their feral
spirit.  Their feral nature is overpowering, as therianthropes live by
instinct and the thrill of the hunt.  Their coats are striped and well
furred.  Their ears are long and well formed for sound detection. 
Their eyes are sharp and piercing.  {x
